  "hashtags" : [ ],
  "sections" : [ {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 1",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "One sat alone beside the highway begging,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 16
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 33
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "His eyes were blind, the light he could not see;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 44
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "He clutched his rags and shivered in the shadows,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 25
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 41
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then Jesus came and bade his darkness flee.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 38
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "chorus",
    "label" : "Chorus",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "When Jesus comes the tempter's pow'r is broken;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 0
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 21
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 40
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "When Jesus comes the tears are wiped away.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 38
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "He takes the gloom and fills the life with glory,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 23
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 43
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "For all is changed when Jesus comes to stay.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 24
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 39
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 2",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "From home and friends the evil spirits drove him,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 26
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 39
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Among the tombs he dwelt in misery;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 1
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 32
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "He cut himself as demon pow'rs possessed him,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 34
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then Jesus came and set the captive free.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 36
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 3",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "Unclean ! unclean ! the leper cried in torment,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 2
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 24
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 39
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "The deaf, the dumb, in helplessness stood near;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 42
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "The fever raged, disease had gripped its victim,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 41
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then Jesus came and cast out every fear.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 35
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 4",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "So men today have found the Saviour able,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 18
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 36
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "They could not conquer passion, lust and sin;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 41
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Their broken hearts had left them sad and lonely,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 24
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 42
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Then Jesus came and dwelt Himself within.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 20
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 38
